SUSPECTED OM:Stage trace suggests -0.006m OM occurring under ice. Magnitude of this OM taken into account when back applying found SRC on Jan 14 2023 back to when data becomes usable again Nov 11 2022.
OR = ESTIMATED FREEZE UP TRACE DRAWN TO FOUND MMNT VALUEOverride: Log Linear‌Q(t) = 662e^(-0.006175489024218089t)‌with freehand adjustment‌

RFT COMMENT: Applied SRC backwards to start of record that seems more reliable after some kind of gas issue or slushing maybe. SRC modified as logger value seems to have been misrecorded on front sheet.BA20230712 - Comp lead agrees with application of SRC back from first winter visit. BA double checked calculation by RFT following miss recorded value on front sheet.  eHSN produced an SRC of 1.827m however logger value for time of DWL was recorded incorrectly during Jan 14 2023 visit. SRC of 1.437m is the confirmed corrected value. A small suspected OM on Jan 7 2023 of -0.006m is found between the point were data becomes usable again (Nov 11 2022) and the visit on Jan 14 2023. Therefore two offsets have been applied as follows:OFFSET 1 = 1.437 - (-0.006) = 1.443m from 2022-11-11 11:50:00 to 2023-01-14 10:40:00OFFSET 2 = -0.006m from 2023-01-07 10:40:00 to 2023-01-14 10:40:00
DR = SEE NOTE IN STAGE WORKING FOR 10ED001 REGARDING UNUSABLE STAGE DATA DURING THIS PERIOD. ESTIMATES OF DISCHARGE DURING THIS TIME ARE BASED ON AVAILABLE STAGE AND DISCHARGE AT 10ED002 AND 10BE001.
